org.javimmutable.collections.hash.hamt

Class HamtLeafNode<T,K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.javimmutable.collections.hash.hamt.HamtLeafNode<T,K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Cursorable<T>, HamtNode<T,K,V>, InvariantCheckable, SplitableIterable<T>

    public class HamtLeafNode<T,K,V>
extends Object
implements HamtNode<T,K,V>
    HamtNode that stores only one value. Any assign that would progress down the tree below this node replaces it with a normal node instead. These exist to shorten the height of the overall tree structure when hashCodes are dispersed.
